parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A broken spare tire carrier can cause the spare tire to fall off while driving, leading to accidents or serious injuries.
A broken door check can cause the door to open wider than intended, making it difficult to exit the vehicle, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
Malfunctioning sliding doors can cause difficulties in entering or exiting the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Sliding doors do not open or close
loud noises when opening or closing doors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking dashboards can cause a distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
Inadequate rear crash protection can cause injuries or fatalities to passengers in the third-row seat.
symptoms: Third-row bench seat moves forward in a rear-end collision
crushing legs and potentially causing fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of VSC can cause the vehicle to suddenly brake or steer, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-misses.
symptoms: the vehicle brakes or steers suddenly
the vehicle slows down or accelerates unexpectedly
and the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
and the power steering pump makes a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion system can cause the power steering to fail, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
and the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft pulley can cause the engine to stall or fail, leading to loss of power and control.
symptoms: and the crankshaft pulley makes a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat belts to retract properly can cause the belts to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to use them, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: preventing them from retracting properly; the belts become stuck in the retraction mechanism; the belts do not return to their normal position; the belts have too much slack.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The jamming and folding of the seat belts can cause them to become unusable, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat belts get twisted and stuck; the belts fold over on themselves; the belts become jammed in the retraction mechanism; the belts do not extend or retract properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the belts to become stuck or unusable, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat belts do not retract properly; the belts become stuck in the retraction mechanism; the belts do not return to their normal position; the belts have too much slack.
